      "message": "Please see PS1 to PS4 for fixes. The 4 changes are:\n\n1) GrSurfaceFillContext::Make that takes a GrBackendFormat now also takes SkBudgeted and that is now properly propagated from GrSurfaceProxy::Copy.\n\n2) Unnecessary GrImageInfo var is removed before call to Make in GrSurfaceProxy::Copy.\n\n3) Assert in GrSurfaceFillContext::Make is updated to not check abandonded state, fixes preabandon debug bot.\n\n4) Correct local matrix is used for yuv-\u003ergba in image lazy\n\n4 was caught by a canvas kit image test. We are supposed to have a set of orientation gms that exercise this. It turns out when I expanded the test I used imagemagick to generate images. It\u0027s orient flag doesn\u0027t seem to work and so all the images are actually stored with an Undefined tag and are actually top-left. I\u0027m working on that in another change.\n",
